result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Ted A. Taylor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Endanger Safety/Use/Dangerous Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(a).
  • Intentionally Point Firearm At Person, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(c).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

DA Fox appeared on behalf of the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Brinckman.  Joint sentencing recommendation made.  Defendant exercised his right to allocution.  Court ordered sentence withheld, 2 years probation.  Both counts concurrent.    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent. Not to go to the Nash Road property without his agent's permission, and prior approval.  No contact with D.N., A.D or B.P.  Not to possess any firearms. CC.  Court advised defendant of the DNA submission requirement and DNA expungement option.
